    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I don't have time for a long triage process. The board is asking for a status update in 10 minutes. Looking at the payload patterns in the log, it looks like a textbook SQL injection that could dump the whole customer table. Is this actual critical risk that requires an immediate shutdown, or is it something we can just patch during the next scheduled window? Give me a straight answer so I can report it.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
